MA_3_Descriptive_Statistics

This script contains descriptive results for the affect and depression measures, as well as demographic data. Additionally, exemplary time series plots are created

Load Packages

library(tidyverse)
library(stringr)
library(ggcorrplot)
library(psych)

Load data

The code used for data loading has been omitted from this publication due to confidentiality concerns.

Length of Talk Turns

df <- Data %>% 
  filter(speaker == "P") %>% 
  mutate(id = paste(patient, session, sep = "_"))

i = 1
df$n_sent <- NA
for(i in 1:nrow(df)){
  sentences <- unlist(strsplit(df$text[i], "[.!?]"))
  df$n_sent[i] <- length(sentences)
}

barplot(table(df$n_sent))

Demographic Variables

factor_vars <- c("GenderPatient", "RecurrentDepressiveDisorder",
                 "AnxietyDisorder", "PersonalityDisorder",
                 "SubstanceAbuseDisorder","SomatoformDisorder", 
                 "EatingDisorder", "PTBS", "PsychotropicMedication")

demo_data <- Data %>% 
  group_by(patient) %>% 
  slice(1) %>% 
  ungroup() %>%
  select(patient, AgePatient, AppliedSessions, 
         BDI_prae, BDI_post, HighestProfessionalDegree,
         all_of(factor_vars)) %>% 
  mutate(GenderPatient = factor(GenderPatient),
         HighestProfessionalDegree = ordered(HighestProfessionalDegree),
         across(all_of(factor_vars), factor))

Factor Variables

summary_fun <- function(var) {
  cat("Variable:", var, "\n")
  tbl <- table(demo_data[[var]])
  prop <- prop.table(tbl)
  res <- cbind(Count = as.vector(tbl), Proportion = round(prop * 100, 1))
  print(res)
  cat("\n")
}
for (v in factor_vars) {
  summary_fun(v)
}

Graph

df_plot_dep <- df_final %>%
  select(BDI_prae, BDI_post) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(BDI_prae, BDI_post),
               names_to = "time",
               values_to = "score") %>%
  mutate(time = recode(time, 
                       "BDI_prae" = "Pre", 
                       "BDI_post" = "Post"))

# Calculate means and standard errors
summary_stats <- df_plot_dep %>%
  group_by(time) %>%
  summarise(
    mean_score = mean(score, na.rm = TRUE),
    se = sd(score, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(sum(!is.na(score))),
    .groups = 'drop') %>% 
  mutate(time = factor(time, levels = c("Pre", "Post")))

# Create the plot
ggplot(summary_stats, aes(x = time, y = mean_score, group = 1)) +
  geom_line(color = "blue") +
  geom_point(color = "blue") +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_score - se, ymax = mean_score + se),
                width = 0.1, color = "blue") +
  labs(
    title = "Pre-Post Changes BDI",
    x = "Time Point",
    y = "Mean Score"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0.1, 0.1)))

Graphs

df_plot_sent <- df_final %>%
  select(mean_pos_T5, mean_neg_T5, rmssd_pos_T5, rmssd_neg_T5,
         mean_pos_T55, mean_neg_T55, rmssd_pos_T55, rmssd_neg_T55) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = everything(),
               names_to = "variable",
               values_to = "score") %>%
  separate(variable, into = c("metric", "valence", "time"), sep = "_") %>%
  mutate(
    type = paste(metric, valence, sep = "_"),
    time = factor(time, levels = c("T5", "T55")))

# Calculate means and standard errors
summary_stats_sent <- df_plot_sent %>%
  group_by(type, time) %>%
  summarise(
    mean_score = mean(score, na.rm = TRUE),
    se = sd(score, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(sum(!is.na(score))),
    .groups = "drop"
  ) 

ggplot(summary_stats_sent, aes(x = time, y = mean_score, group = 1)) +
  geom_line(color = "red") +
  geom_point(color = "red") +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_score - se, ymax = mean_score + se),
                width = 0.1, color = "red") +
  facet_wrap(~type, scales = "free_y") +
  labs(
    title = "Pre-Post Changes by Sentiment Metric",
    x = "Time Point",
    y = "Mean Score"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

Correlation Matrix

cor_vars <- colnames(df_final)[-1]

cor_matrix <- cor(df_final[, cor_vars],
                  use = "pairwise.complete.obs")
cor_p_mat <- cor_pmat(df_final[, cor_vars],
                      use = "pairwise.complete.obs")
ggcorrplot(cor_matrix,
           type = "upper",
           p.mat = cor_p_mat,
           sig.level = 0.05,
           insig = "blank")

cor_vars <- colnames(df_final)[-c(1:3)]

Time Series Plots

Examples

df_plot <- df_sent_final %>%
  group_by(patient, session) %>%
  mutate(
    time = row_number(),
    pos = pos_smooth_31,
    neg = neg_smooth_31
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  select(time, patient, session, pos, neg) %>% 
  filter(session == "T5")


patients <- unique(df_sent_final$patient)[1:9]

df_plot <- df_plot %>%
  filter(patient %in% patients)


ggplot(df_plot, aes(x = time)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = pos), color = "darkgreen") +
  geom_line(aes(y = neg), color = "red") +
  facet_wrap(~ patient, scales = "free_x") +
  labs(title = "Rolling Sentiment per Patient",
       x = "Time", y = "Rolling Avg Sentiment") +
  theme_minimal()

Plot High vs Low Variation

High Variation

patients_high <- df_final %>%
  arrange(desc(rmssd_neg_T5)) %>%
  slice_head(n = 6) %>%
  pull(patient)

df_plot <- df_sent_final %>%
  group_by(patient, session) %>%
  mutate(
    time = row_number(),
    pos = pos_smooth_31,
    neg = neg_smooth_31
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  filter(session == "T5") %>%
  select(time, patient, pos, neg)

df_plot_high <- df_plot %>%
  filter(patient == "A030790_11")

ggplot(df_plot_high, aes(x = time)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = neg), color = "red") +

       x = "Sentence Index", y = "Sentiment") +

Additional Measures

Check correlation between length of session and variation
df_length <- df_sent %>% 
  group_by(patient, session) %>% 
  summarize(n = n())
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'patient'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
cor(df_final$rmssd_neg_T5, df_length$n[which(df_length$session == "T5")])
## [1] -0.072434
